maller room with two doors on each side. they are dead ends.  Past that you have a choice of either going through a door, or hanging a left.  The room past the door leads to a passage to a big room with the goblin archeologist.  The passage left leads to the room where the goblin preacher spawns.  The preacher is guarded by at least 3 other spawns which could be anything  from normal gobs to casters.<br>
<br>
If you go right from the flag room you will eventually get to a gate.  Past the gate and left will take you to the king room.  Its a big room and its covered with goblins.  The ones at the front are regualar goblins, however there is a ramp that leads to the toughest goblins in the zone.  That is our eventual goal.  The mobs that spawn at the bottom of the pit all see invis, so beware.  They are as follows:  goblin honor guards which drop the one handed and two handed silvery axes, goblin patriarch which drops the goblin frost totem, goblin sage no special drop,  High priest Zaharn who drops zaharn's coronet, and the goblin king himself which drops bracers of vox as a common and white wolfhide cloak as his rare.  BTW the wolfhide cloak is worth about 2kpp so its hunted a lot by high levels.  Past the pit in the king room there are a set of BIG double doors.  Past those are the ice giant diplomat.  Dont let the name scare you he isnt nearly as tough as the ice giants outside, though he can hit as hard as a regular giant.  However he is a caster, and he has a special shield up that makes him immune to magic attacks outside of his melee range.  Basically if we were to take him down, all of us would have to get to melee range of him to do any damage.  The diplomat is a ph for the goblin champion who spawns right after he dies<br>
<br>
<br>
Past the diplomat are regular ice giants, giant wooly spiders, icy terrors, giant polar bears, and the Priest of Nagafen.  ALL of them are at least lvl 50+ and hit for at least 120, and are the final barrier to Lady Vox herself.<br>
<br>
As for the other three named spawns, the alchemist, scryer, and the jailer, ill explain where they are at and how to get to them a few days before the raid.<br>
<br>
Balky Bartokimous<br>
25 ( and climbing) druid of Prexus<br>
